## 1. Hardware Requirements

| Item | Requirement |
|---|---|
| **Device** | Raspberry Pi 3B+ or newer (Pi 4 / Pi 5 recommended for performance) |
| **Storage** | MicroSD card — 8 GB minimum, 16 GB+ recommended |
| **Network Interfaces** | **Two** interfaces required — one for the hotspot, one for uplink internet |
| **Uplink** | Any of: Ethernet (`eth0`), second USB WiFi adapter, or 4G/LTE dongle |
| **Hotspot Interface** | Built-in WiFi (`wlan0`) or a dedicated USB WiFi adapter |
| **Power** | Official Raspberry Pi power supply (5V/3A for Pi 4+) |

> **Tip:** The most common configuration is `wlan0` as the managed hotspot and `eth0` as the wired internet uplink. Adjust interface names throughout this guide to match your setup.

