## 2. Operating System Setup

### Flash Raspberry Pi OS

1. Download **Raspberry Pi OS Lite** (64-bit recommended) from [raspberrypi.com/software](https://www.raspberrypi.com/software/).
2. Flash it to your MicroSD card using **Raspberry Pi Imager** or **Balena Etcher**.
3. Before writing, use the Imager's **Advanced Settings** (⚙️) to:
   - Set hostname (e.g., `wipay`)
   - Enable SSH
   - Set your WiFi credentials for initial setup (you can remove this later)
   - Set a username and password

### First Boot

```bash
# SSH into your Pi
ssh pi@wipay.local

# Update the system
sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y
```

