## 3. Network Interface Configuration

WiPay needs `hostapd` and `dnsmasq` to create and manage the WiFi hotspot network.

### Install Access Point Tools

```bash
sudo apt install -y hostapd dnsmasq
```

### Configure the Hotspot Interface (Static IP)

Edit the DHCP client configuration to give `wlan0` a static IP:

```bash
sudo nano /etc/dhcpcd.conf
```

Add to the end of the file:

```
interface wlan0
  static ip_address=192.168.50.1/24
  nohook wpa_supplicant
```

### Configure hostapd (Access Point)

```bash
sudo nano /etc/hostapd/hostapd.conf
```

```ini
interface=wlan0
driver=nl80211
ssid=WiPay-Hotspot
hw_mode=g
channel=6
wmm_enabled=0
macaddr_acl=0
auth_algs=1
ignore_broadcast_ssid=0
```

Enable hostapd:

```bash
sudo systemctl unmask hostapd
sudo systemctl enable hostapd
```

### Configure dnsmasq (DHCP + DNS for Clients)

Back up the default config and create a new one:

```bash
sudo mv /etc/dnsmasq.conf /etc/dnsmasq.conf.bak
sudo nano /etc/dnsmasq.conf
```

```ini
interface=wlan0
dhcp-range=192.168.50.10,192.168.50.250,255.255.255.0,24h
domain=local
address=/#/192.168.50.1
```

> The `address=/#/192.168.50.1` line makes **all DNS queries** resolve to the Pi's IP — this is what triggers the captive portal popup on most devices.

Restart networking services:

```bash
sudo systemctl restart dhcpcd
sudo systemctl restart dnsmasq
```

