## 5. Configuring the Project Files

### Clone the Repository

```bash
cd /opt
sudo git clone https://github.com/makeitwork0/WIPAY.git captive-portal
sudo chown -R $USER:$USER /opt/captive-portal
cd /opt/captive-portal/Project-files
```

### Configure `tunnel_mailer.py` (for Remote Access)

Open the file and update the configuration block at the top:

```bash
nano tunnel_mailer.py
```

```python
# --- CONFIGURATION ---
EMAIL_SENDER   = "your_gmail@gmail.com"
EMAIL_PASSWORD = "your_app_password"    # Gmail App Password — NOT your login password
EMAIL_RECEIVER = "your_gmail@gmail.com" # Where to receive the tunnel URL
PORTAL_PORT    = "8081"                 # Must match the port app4.py runs on
```

> **How to create a Gmail App Password:**
> 1. Go to [myaccount.google.com/security](https://myaccount.google.com/security)
> 2. Enable **2-Step Verification** if not already on
> 3. Go to **App Passwords** → Create a new one → Copy the 16-character password
> 4. Paste it (without spaces) as `EMAIL_PASSWORD`

### Verify `setup_firewall.sh` Interface Names

```bash
nano setup_firewall.sh
```

Check that these match your actual interface names:

```bash
HOTSPOT_IF="wlan0"    # The interface clients connect to
INTERNET_IF="eth0"    # The interface with internet access
PORTAL_PORT="8080"
GATEWAY_IP="192.168.50.1"
```

Run `ip link show` to list your interfaces and confirm the names.

