## 6. Firewall Setup

Make the firewall script executable and run it:

```bash
chmod +x setup_firewall.sh
sudo ./setup_firewall.sh
```

You should see:

```
Setting up Captive Portal Firewall...
Firewall setup complete!
```

### What this script does:

- Enables IPv4 packet forwarding (`/proc/sys/net/ipv4/ip_forward = 1`)
- Flushes existing iptables rules to start clean
- Sets up NAT masquerading so clients share the Pi's internet connection
- Creates a `CAPTIVE_PORTAL` iptables chain that redirects all HTTP (port 80) traffic to Flask on port 8080
- Configures a `FORWARD` chain that blocks all traffic by default — Flask grants access per-device dynamically
- Creates a `tc` HTB bandwidth tree on the hotspot interface for per-user speed limiting

### Make Firewall Rules Persistent

Install `iptables-persistent` to restore rules on reboot:

```bash
sudo apt install iptables-persistent -y
# When prompted, choose YES to save current rules
```

To save rules manually at any time:

```bash
sudo netfilter-persistent save
```

