## 8. Launching the Application

### Set the Admin Secret

The app **will not start** without the `ADMIN_SECRET` environment variable. Choose a strong, random password:

```bash
export ADMIN_SECRET="replace_this_with_a_strong_password"
```

### Run the Flask App

```bash
cd /opt/captive-portal/Project-files
sudo -E python3 app4.py
```

> `sudo` is required because the app uses `iptables` and `tc` system commands to control traffic.  
> `-E` preserves your environment variables (including `ADMIN_SECRET`) when escalating to root.

### Verify It's Running

From another device connected to your hotspot, open any HTTP URL — you should be redirected to the WiPay portal page.

From the Pi itself:

```bash
curl http://192.168.50.1:8080
```

