## 10. Running as a System Service

Set up WiPay to start automatically on boot using `systemd`.

### Create the Flask App Service

```bash
sudo nano /etc/systemd/system/wipay.service
```

```ini
[Unit]
Description=WiPay Captive Portal
After=network.target

[Service]
Type=simple
User=root
WorkingDirectory=/opt/captive-portal/Project-files
Environment="ADMIN_SECRET=replace_this_with_a_strong_password"
ExecStart=/usr/bin/python3 /opt/captive-portal/Project-files/app4.py
Restart=always
RestartSec=5

[Install]
WantedBy=multi-user.target
```

### Create the Tunnel Mailer Service (Optional)

```bash
sudo nano /etc/systemd/system/wipay-tunnel.service
```

```ini
[Unit]
Description=WiPay Cloudflare Tunnel Mailer
After=wipay.service
Requires=wipay.service

[Service]
Type=simple
User=root
WorkingDirectory=/opt/captive-portal/Project-files
ExecStart=/usr/bin/python3 /opt/captive-portal/Project-files/tunnel_mailer.py
Restart=always
RestartSec=10

[Install]
WantedBy=multi-user.target
```

### Enable and Start Services

```bash
sudo systemctl daemon-reload
sudo systemctl enable wipay.service
sudo systemctl enable wipay-tunnel.service
sudo systemctl start wipay.service
sudo systemctl start wipay-tunnel.service
```

### Check Service Status

```bash
sudo systemctl status wipay.service
sudo journalctl -u wipay.service -f    # Live logs
```

